{"id":391,"date":"2011-01-20T01:31:31","date_gmt":"2011-01-20T05:31:31","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=391"},"modified":"2024-08-19T09:29:21","modified_gmt":"2024-08-19T05:29:21","slug":"rights-allah-tawheed","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/01\/20\/rights-allah-tawheed\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Monotheism: Rights of Allah upon His servants"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Mu&#8217;adh bin Jabal reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, &#8220;<strong>O Mu&#8217;adh, do you know what the right of Allah is upon His servants?<\/strong>&#8221; I said, &#8220;Allah and His Messenger know best.&#8221; The Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>To worship Him alone and to associate none in worship with Him. And do you know what their right is upon Him?<\/strong>&#8221; I said, &#8220;Allah and His Messenger know best.&#8221; The Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>Not to punish them if they do so.<\/strong>&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 7373, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 30<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/strong><\/em>\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0630\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u062c\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0644\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064f\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0645\u064f\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0630\u064f \u0623\u064e\u062a\u064e\u062f\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u062d\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0